What an amazing first week! While teachers and administration have spent countless hours this summer preparing for the school year, none of us could have predicted how well the first week would go!

By Thursday, we had 98% attendance and participation in our virtual classes!!

While we wish we could see you all in-person, you have been amazing in your online presence and participation. We are so proud of our JPEC students and families!

Keep up the hard work!

post_text:
Say hello to Ms. Shirk, our Art Teacher! She has been thinking so creatively on how to give our Falcons a great art experience!

"It has been really nice to see our students and begin working with them again - I missed them all so much! My students had excellent attendance and participation this week. I was impressed by how well they have remembered to log into our daily Zoom meetings on time, as well as how comfortable they seem using Schoology to complete their assignments. While we all navigate together what school looks like and feels like this term, it is heartening to know that my students' commitment to their education remains strong. We are all in this together, and can continue to encourage each other to do our best, to take care of ourselves every day, and to work together to create a positive online learning community for as long as we need it in order to keep one other healthy and safe."

post_text:
Falcons, meet one of our fabulous EC math teachers, Ms. Lloyd. Here's what she has to say about the first few days of school!

‚ÄùThe students seem to be adjusting quite well to learning math online! I have created notes and videos to help students, so they are able to use those resources to work ahead or go back to relearn a skill. We are also still providing daily instruction as well. I'm really excited about our Wednesday office hours: time dedicated to work one-on-one or with small groups to help students progress in math. Stop by and see your math teachers every Wednesday from 9-11 a.m. and 12:30-2:30 p.m. via Zoom!‚Äù

College Prep (grades 6-8) volleyball try-outs will be this Wednesday (9/2) and Thursday (9/3) only. Athletes only need to attend one of the two sessions, but it is recommended to come to both. Please make sure to have a valid sports physical or the health questionnaire that states you had a physical last year.

If you have any questions, please contact Mr. Serafin Llerena at serafin.llerena@jacksonpec.org or 517-888-4137.

post_text: Way to go, Ben Tripp!
shared_text:
Jackson Area Career Center
July 15 at 11:31 AM ¬∑

CONGRATS are in order for a few of our Visual Communications students!

Julio Hernandez - Michigan Center, Senior; Ben Tripp - JPEC, Junior; and Taryn Ratliff - East Jackson, Junior, took some time out of their summer vacation to test for Adobe certification for Photoshop - and all three passed!

The Adobe Certified Associate certification is an industry-recognized credential that effectively validates one's expertise - proving they have the skills and knowledge to meet the demands of today's design industry.

post_text:
Falcon Families, it is with heavy hearts and great sadness that we share of the passing of a former JPEC student. We learned of this tragic news this morning, and while we are not able to disclose details, our students have begun to hear about this tragedy.

We are providing additional support for our students as they process their emotions through our Counselor, Mrs. Yonnick, our Dean of Students, Mr. Llerena, and any additional support we may need from the Oasis Center on campus. Our staff will be sensitive and understanding of our students' needs and support in every way possible. We ask as details come to your attention that you respect the privacy of the family and refrain from revealing names and details on our social media.

Please know that we are here to be supportive during what can be a very difficult and confusing time. Please contact your school leader or me directly with any questions or concerns.

Sincerely,

Shane Malmquist

We would like to remind all seventh grade students that tomorrow Tuesday October 29th is Challenge Day. Students should arrive to EIC by 7:45am.
